To find the probability of getting four of a kind in a poker hand, we first need to understand what four of a kind means. It means having four cards of the same face value and one card of a different face value.

## Step 2
The total number of ways to draw 5 cards from a deck of 52 is calculated using combinations since the order of drawing the cards does not matter. The formula for combinations is C(n, k) = n! / [k!(n - k)!], where n is the total number of items, k is the number of items to choose, and "!" denotes factorial, the product of all positive integers up to that number. So, the total number of 5-card hands is C(52, 5).

## Step 3
Calculating C(52, 5) gives us the total number of possible poker hands. C(52, 5) = 52! / [5!(52 - 5)!] = 52! / (5! * 47!) = (52 × 51 × 50 × 49 × 48) / (5 × 4 × 3 × 2 × 1) = 2,598,960.

## Step 4
To get four of a kind, we first choose the face value of the four cards, which can be done in C(13, 1) ways since there are 13 different face values (Ace through King). Then, we choose 4 out of the 4 cards of that face value, which is C(4, 4). After that, we choose 1 card out of the remaining 48 cards that are not of the chosen face value, which can be done in C(48, 1) ways.

## Step 5
The number of ways to get four of a kind is C(13, 1) × C(4, 4) × C(48, 1) = 13 × 1 × 48 = 624.

## Step 6
The probability of getting four of a kind is the number of favorable outcomes (getting four of a kind) divided by the total number of outcomes (total number of 5-card hands). So, the probability = 624 / 2,598,960.

## Step 7
Now, we calculate the probability. Probability = 624 / 2,598,960 = 0.000240096.

